description: A driveway is a service road leading to a residence or business
A parking aisle is a subordinated way in a parking lot between rows of parking spaces that vehicles use to drive into and out of the spaces.
An alley is a service road usually located between properties for access to utilities.
Relatively short lengths of track, running parallel to (and connected to) a main route.
Tracks within [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rail_yard rail yards] operated by the same company as one operating main line
Relatively short lengths of track, built to give one company or entity access to the main line, normally for freight-only use.
A drive-through way where customers can purchase products without leaving their cars.
A way for firefighters to reach a building
Dedicated bus service lane or road typically found at bus stations
